Skyesol command runbook (copy/paste friendly)

1) One-time setup (inside repo)
- cd /workspaces/skyesol
- npm install

2) Keep Case Studies index + sitemap in sync
- npm run content:sync

What this does now:
- Runs case-studies index sync first
- Then regenerates sitemap

You can also run each step directly:
- npm run case-studies:sync
- npm run gen-sitemap

3) Build command (now includes sync+sitemap flow)
- npm run build

4) Local server options
A) Quick static preview (no Netlify Functions)
- cd /workspaces/skyesol
- python3 -m http.server 8080
- Open: http://localhost:8080

B) Full local platform preview (with Netlify Functions)
- cd /workspaces/skyesol
- npx netlify dev
- Open: http://localhost:8888

5) Netlify deploy flow
- cd /workspaces/skyesol
- npm install
- npx netlify login
- npx netlify init
- npm run content:sync
- npx netlify deploy --prod

6) Useful maintenance commands
- npm run link-check
- npm run link-check:fix
- npm run meta:check
- npm run meta:apply

7) Typical daily sequence
- cd /workspaces/skyesol
- npm run content:sync
- npm run link-check
- npx netlify dev
